{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "64b16a5ff23ac7d519f9b3d2", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76cfc52ffa3c944600e0"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fec2b295b085ab6eb91"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "615d92eede3d91842a5cf82b", "title": "JEE Advanced 2017 (Paper 2)", "isVisible": true}], "position": 0, "type": "multipleCorrect", "level": 2, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "question": {"text": "<p>A wheel of radius R and mass M is placed at the bottom of a fixed step of height R as shown in the figure. A constant force is continuously applied on the surface of the wheel so that it just climbs the step without slipping. Consider the torque <math><mi>\u03c4</mi></math> about an axis normal to the plane of the paper passing through the point Q. Which of the following options is/are correct?<br ><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/lutgkulkqbltyxuimlbgmsfbvxuczjxoryrrecjcnmrjddyrsk.jpeg\"/></p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "A0pLZ", "text": "If the force is applied normal to the circumference at point  <math><mi>X</mi></math>  then  <math><mi>\u03c4</mi></math>  is constant", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "65uXs", "text": "If the force is applied tangentially at point S then  <math><mi>\u03c4</mi><mo>\u2260</mo><mn>0</mn></math>  but the wheel never climbs the step", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "p6GcN", "text": "If the force is applied normal to the circumference at point P then <math><mi>&tau;</mi></math> is zero", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "19fT4", "text": "If the force is applied at point P tangentially then  <math><mi>\u03c4</mi></math>  decreases continuously as the wheel climbs", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>(i) is incorrect.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/11_solu_phy_pa_2.jpg\"/></p><p>If force is applied normal to surface at point <math><mi>X</mi></math></p><p><math><mi>\u03c4</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow></msub><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>R</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi>\u03b8</mi></mrow></mrow></math></p><p>Thus <math><mi>\u03c4</mi></math> depends on <math><mi>\u03b8</mi></math> and it is not constant</p><p>(ii) is incorrect</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/11_solu_phy_pa_2_1.jpg\"/></p><p>If force applied tangentially at S</p><p><math><mi>\u03c4</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><mi>R</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mo>\u2260</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>But it will climb as mentioned in question.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/11_solu_phy_pa_2_2.jpg\"/></p><p>If force is applied normal to surface at P then line of action of force will pass from Q and thus\u00a0<math><mi>\u03c4</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>(iv) is incorrect.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/11_solu_phy_pa_2_3.jpg\"/></p><p>If force is applied at P tangentially the <math><mi>\u03c4</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "3f8bd9e940b643bca702c2ebd2642310", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/1zfXGLqwrEbPb.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/1zfXGLqwrEbPb.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ec